topic.title: Something seems fishy here - Conspiracy afoot!
topic.body:
So, I have spent this evening bored out of my mind until I stumbled across this post: http://127.0.0.1:43110/Talk.ZeroNetwork.bit/?Topic:1598405387_148xLrZAr6Bjyhe6spVxJJbFHtdmwbVSCb/Who+was+talking+shit+about+us+again

After spending the past 2-3 hours analyzing all the related info and such it would seem there is definitely something fishy about zaron, kapec, geekless, and otbtechh22f4wcuo going on right now. It seems to me that these four IDs are playing a game of good cop bad cop in order to attract more business for otbtechh22f4wcuo. It is somewhat difficult to tell who is who, but I will say that it does seem that geekless and zaron have made posts indicating that they are very close with the ZeroTalk admin No fish, and otbtechh22f4wcuo seems to be using multiple IDs in an attempt to spread information regarding the Illuminati which in and of itself is a conspiracy theory.

My belief is that zaron/kapec/geekless are closely tied with ZeroNet's admin (NoFish,) and also I think that otbtechh22f4wcuo is an identity that they created as a sort of strawman to attack Donald Trump's campaign and also to convince ZeroTalk users that there is a need for censorship here. This is not acceptable whatsoever in my eyes since this is an abuse of the privilege of being so closely tied to a free speech platform's administration.

You will notice that after otbtechh22f4wcuo came around, there began talk of censorship here on a platform that was originally intended to be censorship resistant. This further adds to my belief that otbtechh22f4wcuo is being used as a way for NoFish/Kapec/Zaron/Geekless to manipulate the truth about what is happening. Zaron and Geekless claim the censorship is only to prevent "spam" and CP, but its funny how there was no mention of it until this otbtechh22f4wcuo character showed up on ZeroTalk. This makes me think they are simply trying to find ways to regulate information to skew the public opinion so as to influence their voting decisions just like other platforms such as Twitter and Facebook have been doing this past few months. 

It seems to me as if all of these individuals may even conspiring to remove the freedom of speech aspect from ZeroTalk and simultaneously using otbtechh22f4wcuo as a strawman to influence public opinion and boost his sales since they are all likely close friends. Again, this is pretty much what Twitter and Facebook as well as all other mainstream media platforms are doing to influence voter opinion in America right now. Its just how politics seems to work anymore really!

These are just my thoughts after a few hours of reading up on what has transpired so far. I am very interested in what will come of this especially since most recently kapec threatened to essentially doxx otbtechh22f4wcuo. That's either a low blow or again as I said this is an attempt to convince their audience that censorship is needed on ZeroTalk.
